HEADWORD: Oberon
<hw>Ob"er*on</hw> <pr>(⟦ocr⟧b"⟦etil⟧r*⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[F., fr. OF. <ets>Auberon</ets>; prob. of Frankish origin.]</ety>
<fld>(Mediaeval Mythol.)</fld> <def>The king of the fairies, and husband
of <persfn>Titania</persfn> or <person>Queen Mab</person>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
